Hide the native barter (trade) window AND the player inventory window (scoped to
GM_Barter) when the HUD is hidden via "Hide UI", so the companion (bottom-screen)
barter UI is the sole barter surface while Hide UI is active; restore both when
Hide UI is toggled back on. Same pattern as companion-hide-container-on-hideui.patch.

Hunk 1 — trade window. Gate = mHudEnabled && containsMode(GM_Barter). containsMode
(not getMode()==GM_Barter) is correct: nothing is pushed on top of the trade window
during barter, and it matches TradeWindow::onClose()'s containsMode(GM_Barter)
early-return (tradewindow.cpp), which is why hiding mid-barter neither resets the
reference nor ends the session.

Hunk 2 — player inventory window. GM_Barter's GuiModeState shows BOTH the trade
window and the inventory window, so hunk 1 alone leaves the inventory window on the
top screen. Hidden only during barter under Hide UI (scoped to GM_Barter), placed
AFTER the vanilla line that unconditionally re-shows the inventory window for
GM_Barter (same override trap the container patch documents).

Hunk 3 — barter close signal (COMPANION_BARTER_CLOSED) when hidden. Emitted in
TradeWindow::onClose() (companion-barter-export.patch), which WindowBase::setVisible
(false) only fires on a visible->hidden transition. Once hunk 1 has hidden the trade
window, the mode-pop's setVisible(false) is a no-op, so onClose() never fires and the
overlay sticks open. Capture whether the trade window was already hidden before the
pop and call onClose() explicitly after mGuiModeStates[mode].update(false), when
containsMode(GM_Barter) is false so the onClose guard passes. The !isVisible() gate
avoids a double-emit in the native-visible case. Mirrors the container patch's
pickpocket-finish-on-pop fix exactly.

--- a/apps/openmw/mwgui/windowmanagerimp.cpp
+++ b/apps/openmw/mwgui/windowmanagerimp.cpp
@@ -679,6 +679,15 @@
         if (mContainerWindow)
             mContainerWindow->setVisible(mHudEnabled && containsMode(GM_Container));
 
+        // COMPANION: hide the barter (trade) window with Hide UI so the companion bottom
+        // screen is the sole barter surface; restore it when Hide UI toggles back on.
+        // TradeWindow::onClose() early-returns while containsMode(GM_Barter) (tradewindow.cpp),
+        // so hiding it mid-barter neither resets the reference nor ends the session — that only
+        // happens when GM_Barter is actually removed. The player inventory window (also part of
+        // GM_Barter's GuiModeState) is hidden a few lines below, next to the GM_Container case.
+        if (mTradeWindow)
+            mTradeWindow->setVisible(mHudEnabled && containsMode(GM_Barter));
+
         bool gameMode = !isGuiMode();
 
         MWBase::Environment::get().getInputManager()->changeInputMode(!gameMode);
@@ -740,6 +749,13 @@
             // ItemTransfer target when Hide UI is toggled back on, so nothing breaks.
             if (mInventoryWindow && !mHudEnabled && getMode() == GM_Container)
                 mInventoryWindow->setVisible(false);
+            // COMPANION: same for barter — GM_Barter's GuiModeState shows BOTH the trade
+            // window and the inventory window, so the inventory window must be hidden too
+            // under Hide UI (scoped to GM_Barter). Same override caveat as the GM_Container
+            // line above: it must come after the vanilla setVisible line, which unconditionally
+            // re-shows the inventory window for GM_Barter.
+            if (mInventoryWindow && !mHudEnabled && getMode() == GM_Barter)
+                mInventoryWindow->setVisible(false);
         }
 
         GuiMode mode = mGuiModes.back();
@@ -1541,10 +1557,21 @@
                 // so we must not double-run — hence the !isVisible() gate.
                 const bool containerHiddenOnPop
                     = (mode == GM_Container && mContainerWindow && !mContainerWindow->isVisible());
+                // COMPANION: same for barter — if the trade window was already hidden by the
+                // Hide UI gate above, the update(false) below is a no-op setVisible(false) that
+                // will NOT fire TradeWindow::onClose(), so COMPANION_BARTER_CLOSED (emitted
+                // there) never reaches the bottom screen and the overlay sticks open. Capture
+                // it here and call onClose() explicitly after the pop (containsMode(GM_Barter)
+                // is now false so the onClose guard passes). The !isVisible() gate avoids a
+                // double-emit in the visible case (update(false) fires onClose itself then).
+                const bool barterHiddenOnPop
+                    = (mode == GM_Barter && mTradeWindow && !mTradeWindow->isVisible());
                 mGuiModes.pop_back();
                 mGuiModeStates[mode].update(false);
                 if (containerHiddenOnPop)
                     mContainerWindow->onClose();
+                if (barterHiddenOnPop)
+                    mTradeWindow->onClose();
                 MWBase::Environment::get().getLuaManager()->uiModeChanged(MWWorld::Ptr());
             }
         }
